COMPONENT NAME: IKM SQL to Siebel Append (EIM)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Integration Knowledge Module - Integrates data into a Siebel EIM (Enterprise Integration Manager) table from any ANSI-SQL92 compliant staging area, then generate the appropriate EIM configuration files (.ifb) and runs the import process using the server Manager. The target table is populated in truncate / insert mode
SRVRMGR is deemed to have succeeded if it runs. The Report step will report the status of the inserted rows. If you want the interface to fail if any rows were not imported, then on the Flow tab of the interface, specify 0 as the Maximum number of errors allowed.
(From 12c onwards, all messages will appear in the Log file. The USE_LOG and LOG_FILE_NAME options are no longer required. )
Restriction: - This module requires srvrmgr on the machine where the agent runs.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Delete the entries for the batch
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Path to create the EIM configuration files (.ifb). This parameter is mandatory.
SRVMGR binary file name, the file name could in lowercase.
Path to the srvrmgr binary. This parameter is mandatory.
Network address of the Gateway Server machine. This parameter is mandatory.
Enterprise Server name. This parameter is mandatory.
Siebel Server name (default is all servers). This parameter is mandatory.
Server administrator user name. This parameter is mandatory.
Server administrator password. This parameter is mandatory.
Debug messages will be written to the agent's stdout. If you want to see the messages, you will need to run a separate (stand-alone) agent.

import java.sql as sql import java.lang as lang import java.lang.Long as long import java.util.logging import time import os.path
# set the logger logger = odiRef.getLogger()
rSQL='''SELECT IF_ROW_STAT STATUS, count(*) NROWS FROM <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> where IF_ROW_BATCH_NUM = '<%=odiRef.getOption("BATCH_ID")%>' GROUP BY IF_ROW_STAT'''
sess=odiRef.getStep("SESS_GUID") nno=odiRef.getStep("NNO")
logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "DEBUG: %s-%s" % (sess,nno)) logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "%s: SQL: %s" % (dbg,rSQL))
trgConn = odiRef.getJDBCConnection("DEST") try: trgStmt = trgConn.createStatement() rs = trgStmt.executeQuery(rSQL)
logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "%s: Query Executed" % dbg )
nbRows=0 status='' nErrs=0
while (rs.next()): nbRows=nbRows+1 logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "%s: Row in result: %s" % (dbg,nbRows)) stat=rs.getString(1) nrows=rs.getString(2) status=status+ "%s: '%s'\n\r" % (stat,nrows) logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "%s: Status: %s" % (dbg,status)) nbrows = long.parseLong(nrows) if stat=="IMPORTED": odiRef.setNbInsert(nbrows) else: nErrs=nErrs + nbrows odiRef.setNbErrors(nErrs) finally: trgConn.close()

import os # #Mandatory Option # SIEBEL_GATEWAY = '<%=odiRef.getOption("SIEBEL_GATEWAY")%>' SIEBEL_ENTERPRISE = '<%=odiRef.getOption("SIEBEL_ENTERPRISE")%>' SIEBEL_SERVER = '<%=odiRef.getOption("SIEBEL_SERVER")%>' SERVER_USER = '<%=odiRef.getOption("SERVER_USER")%>' SERVER_USER_PWD = '<%=odiRef.getOption("SERVER_USER_PWD")%>' SRVRMGR_PATH =r'<%=odiRef.getOption("SRVRMGR_PATH")%>/<%=odiRef.getOption("SRVRMGR")%>' IFB_PATH =r'<%=odiRef.getOption("IFB_PATH")%>' TABLE_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME")%>' STARTTASK = r'run task for component eim with config=ODI_<%=odiRef.getSession("SESS_GUID")%>_IMPORT.ifb, TraceFlags=1, ErrorFlags=1, SQLFlags=8'
cmd = '''%s -g %s -e %s -s %s -u %s -p %s -c "%s" ''' %(SRVRMGR_PATH,SIEBEL_GATEWAY, SIEBEL_ENTERPRISE, SIEBEL_SERVER, SERVER_USER, SERVER_USER_PWD, STARTTASK) if os.system(cmd) <> 0 : raise OdiKMException("ODIKM-STDKM-10009", "ODIKM-STDKM-10009: Error executing OS command: ({0})", [cmd])
